  // Random events — romance arc
  '前锋与门将恋爱': 'The Striker and Goalkeeper Are Dating',
  '你发现队里的前锋与门将开始谈起了恋爱，这使得前锋在球门前感到非常犹豫，因为他总会想到自己的恋人在面对破门时的无助。因此，他已经连续三场错失了绝佳机会。你的决定是：': 'You discover that your striker and goalkeeper have started dating. The striker now hesitates in front of goal, haunted by the thought of how helpless their beloved looks when beaten. Three matches, three golden chances missed. Your decision:',
  '无视': 'Ignore It',
  '祝福他们': 'Give Them Your Blessing',
  '棒打鸳鸯': 'Break Them Up',
  '前锋在空门前再次犹豫，皮球滑门而出。你沉默地看着这一切发生。': 'The striker hesitates in front of another open goal and sends the ball wide. You watch in silence.',
  '“祝你们幸福。”你的话让全队都松了口气，但前锋射门时眼里依然只有门将的身影……': '“I wish you both every happiness.” The squad breathes a sigh of relief, but the striker still sees only the goalkeeper whenever they shoot…',
  '“立刻分手，否则滚出我的球队！”你的强硬让更衣室一片死寂。': '“Break up now, or get out of my team!” Your ultimatum leaves the dressing room deathly silent.',
  '进攻型中场和中锋恋爱': 'The No. 10 and Striker Are Dating',
  '你发现队里的进攻型中场和中锋开始谈起了恋爱，这使得他们的传接变得更有默契，收获多个进球，但也引来了其他球员的不满。他们一致认为，这两位队友从不把球传给别人，是球霸行为。你的决定是：': 'Your attacking midfielder and striker have started dating. Their chemistry has produced plenty of goals, but the rest of the squad is furious: the pair never pass to anyone else. Your decision:',
  '能进球你们做什么都行！祝福他们': 'If You Keep Scoring, Do Whatever You Like! Bless Them',
  '年轻的中场不能遇见太惊艳的中锋！拆散他们': 'A Young Midfielder Should Never Meet a Striker This Irresistible! Break Them Up',
  '他们又进球了，但其他球员越来越沉默。更衣室里开始出现小团体的裂痕。': 'They score again, but the other players grow quieter. Factions begin to split the dressing room.',
  '媒体盛赞你的开明，但更衣室里其他球员呢？你最好不要去想。': 'The press applauds your open-mindedness. As for everyone else in the dressing room? Best not to think about it.',
  '你强行拆散了这对球霸情侣，其他球员如释重负，但场上那种灵性的配合再也回不来了。': 'You force the ball-hogging couple apart. The squad is relieved, but their magical link-up play never returns.',
  '中卫搭档恋爱': 'The Centre-Back Pair Are Dating',
  '你发现队里的两个中卫搭档谈起了恋爱，他们的配合一直很有默契，感情也十分低调。但小报记者似乎已经注意到了这段恋情的端倪。如果记者抓住了证据，他们可能会在媒体上被严肃批评，管理层也可能会质疑你的球队治理能力。你的决定是：': 'Your two centre-backs are dating. Their partnership has always been excellent and the relationship discreet, but the tabloids have caught the scent. Evidence could bring a media storm—and questions from the board about your control of the squad. Your decision:',
  '祝福他们，与他们坚定地站在一起': 'Support Them and Stand Firmly at Their Side',
  '为了球队，你们忍一忍吧！拆散他们': 'For the Team, You Must End It! Break Them Up',
  '第二天小报刊登了他们牵手的照片。两人低着头走进更衣室，队友们的目光让气氛凝固。': 'The next day, the tabloids print a photo of them holding hands. They enter the dressing room with heads bowed as their teammates stare.',
  '你在发布会上公开支持他们，全队感动得热泪盈眶。但管理层的电话在五分钟后打了过来……': 'You publicly support them at the press conference. The squad is moved to tears. Five minutes later, the board calls…',
  '管理层对你的果断表示赞赏，但更衣室则沉默了。': 'The board praises your decisiveness. The dressing room says nothing.',
